    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-28T01:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-28T01:35:00-05:00" n="419"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/14472: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-28T10:00:00+03:25"
                            >August 28, 1941—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>113. The Prime Minister<note n="11a" xml:id="d419fn11a">Mohammed All
                        Foroughi.</note> in presenting the new Cabinet to the Parliament this
                    morning made the important announcement that since <pb facs="0444" n="436"
                        xml:id="pg_436"/> Iran is a peace-loving nation, orders have been given for
                    Iranian forces to cease all resistance to the British and Russians.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
